laboratory_examinations.findings: Multiple hepatic lesions scattered throughout the liver, largest being a 1.6 cm simple cyst in hepatic segment VI. Appendix is fluid-filled and abnormally dilated, measuring up to 1.1 cm, with mucosal hyperenhancement, periappendiceal fat stranding, and adjacent free fluid.
